-- Samsung to spend $1.4 billion to upgrade chip lines
-- 
-- Fri Mar 14, 2008 5:12am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/14/us-samsungelec-investment-idUSSEO27269220080314

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Samsung Electronics Co Ltd ( 005930.KS ), the world's largest memory chip maker, said on Friday it will spend 1.35 trillion won ($1.37 billion) to upgrade semiconductor lines in 2008. 

 It told the Korea Exchange in a filing that the investment was decided at a board meeting. ($1=988.6 Won) (Reporting by Kim Yeon-hee; Editing by Rhee So-eui)